# Environment Variables Template
# ============================================================================
# FRONTEND VARIABLES (Required in .env.local)
# ============================================================================
#
# Convex Connection URL
# Get this from: https://dashboard.convex.dev → Your Project → Settings → Deployment URL
VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://your-project.convex.cloud

# ============================================================================
# BACKEND VARIABLES (Set in Convex Dashboard - NOT in .env.local)
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Backend environment variables must be set in the Convex Dashboard,
# NOT in your .env.local file. This keeps secrets secure and separate from
# frontend configuration.
#
# How to set backend variables:
#   1. Via Convex CLI:
#      npx convex env set VARIABLE_NAME value
#
#   2. Via Convex Dashboard:
#      https://dashboard.convex.dev → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# ============================================================================
# Required Backend Variables (Set in Convex Dashboard)
# ============================================================================
#
# Environment Configuration
  #CONVEX_ENV=development  # or 'production'

# Stripe (Payment Processor)
  #STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...        # Test mode: sk_test_... | Live mode: sk_live_...
  #STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...      # Get from Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks

# PayPal (Payment Processor)
  #PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID=...                 # Sandbox or Live credentials
  #PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET=...             # From PayPal Developer Dashboard
  #PAYPAL_WEBHOOK_ID=...                # From PayPal Webhooks configuration

# Bitcoin (Payment Processor)
  #BITCOIN_NETWORK=testnet              # 'testnet' for development, 'mainnet' for production
  #BITCOIN_MASTER_VPRV=vprv...          # BIP84 testnet extended private key (if using testnet)
  #BITCOIN_MASTER_ZPRV=zprv...          # BIP84 mainnet extended private key (if using mainnet)

# Application Configuration
  #SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000       # Your site URL (optional in development)

# ============================================================================
# Why This Separation?
# ============================================================================
#
# Frontend variables (.env.local):
#   - Safe to expose in browser
#   - Only VITE_CONVEX_URL needed for frontend to connect to Convex
#
# Backend variables (Convex Dashboard):
#   - Never exposed to browser
#   - Secrets stay in Convex's secure environment
#   - No duplicate secrets in multiple places
#   - Single source of truth for backend configuration
#
# ============================================================================
# Development Workflow
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Set VITE_CONVEX_URL in .env.local (get from Convex Dashboard)
#
# 3. Set all backend variables via the Dashboard or via Convex CLI:
#    npx convex env set CONVEX_ENV development
#    npx convex env set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY sk_test_...
#    npx convex env set STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET whsec_...
#    npx convex env set PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID ...
#    npx convex env set PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET ...
#    npx convex env set PAYPAL_WEBHOOK_ID ...
#    npx convex env set BITCOIN_NETWORK testnet
#    npx convex env set BITCOIN_MASTER_VPRV vprv...
#    npx convex env set SITE_URL http://localhost:3000
#
# 4. Start development:
#    pnpm dev  # Starts both Vite and Convex
#
# ============================================================================
# Production Deployment
# ============================================================================
#
# See .github/PRODUCTION_SETUP.md for complete production setup instructions
#
# Key differences:
# - Use live credentials (sk_live_..., production PayPal, mainnet Bitcoin)
# - Set CONVEX_ENV=production
# - Use BITCOIN_NETWORK=mainnet with BITCOIN_MASTER_ZPRV (starts with zprv)
#
